reviews.text: An excellent experience overall where you shop for the seafood you like in your hotpot, then you pay for your desired items, and they deliver your seafood to you at your table with your choice of mild vegetable broth or numbingly spicy broth. While the staff setup and heat your respective hotpots, you are free to partake in buffet style unlimited beverages, rich pork sauce rice bowls, your pick noodles types and flavors, as well as concoct your dipping sauces with condiments. I particularly love the Japanese style soy sauce with sā tsá sauce and minced garlic with a sprinkling of cilantro! The ambiance is lively and adjacent to a calming fountain pool at the foot of a beautiful Japanese cherry blossom tree! On the other side of the cherry blossom wall is the location of both the men's and women's wheelchair NON-accessible restrooms as well as a wheelchair accessible restroom to the right of the men's restrooms. I've ate at a plethora of hotpot restaurants in both the USA and Taiwan, and this experience was by far the most professional and courteous due to attentive wait staff, diligent used utensil collection off your tables, and constant replenishment of all-you-can-eat staples such as pork sauce rice bowls, various noodle packets, and coffee cups and beverage glasses. Initially, I was shown to a table for two that was dirty and not ready for new patrons, so upon voicing my compliant to the wait staff, he immediately summoned the shift leader in all black dress shirt and black slacks. The shift leader apologized for the messy table, showed us to another clean table, delivered us our respective hotpots and seafood purchases, then was very attentive with our table's cleanliness throughout our meal. He was professional and courteous throughout the evening, and even allowed us to stay after closing time for my wife and I to enjoy our conversation and discussions. Even though this is my first time dining at this hotpot restaurant, I will definitely return for future dinners with colleagues, family, and friends. The best part is since you have already prepaid for your seafood items, they will pack up your leftovers for you to take home after your meal! At other hotpot buffets, you are not allowed to take leftovers with you upon departure.
